<p>John Tyler, the 10th president of the United States, was born on 3/29/1790, in Charles City County, Virginia. He was 51 when he took office on 4/4/1841. Member: Whig Party.

	
		He left office on 3/4/1845.
	

	His occupation before the presidency: Lawyer.
	His college: William and Mary.

	
		He died in Richmond, Virginia, on 1/18/1862.
	
</p>

<p><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/John_Tyler">View Wikipedia entry for John Tyler.</a></p>

